Q1: Find Greatest common divisor of a and b (gcd(a,b)) if:
i) a = 5487967 and b = 3880
5487967 = 3880 (1414) + 1647
3880 = 1647 (2) + 586
1647 = 586 (2) + 475
586 = 475 (1) + 111
475 = 111 (4) + 31
111 = 31 (3) + 18
31 = 18 (1) + 13
18 = 13 (1) + 5
13 = 5 (2) + 3
5 = 3 (1) + 2
3 = 2 (1) + 1
2 = 1 (2) + 0
--------
ii) a = 4960 and b = 388077
4960 = 3880 (1) + 1080
3880 = 1080 (3) + 640
1080 = 640 (1) + 440
640 = 440 (1) + 200
440 = 200 (2) + 40
200 = 40 (5) + 0
--------
iii) a = 4960 and b = 3880
4960 = 3880 (1) + 1080
3880 = 1080 (3) + 640
1080 = 640 (1) + 440
640 = 440 (1) + 200
440 = 200 (2) + 40
200 = 40 (5) + 0
--------
